Jose Antonio CORNEJO-VILLAGRANA, Petitioner,
v.
Jefferson B. SESSIONS III, Attorney General, Respondent. No. 13-72185 United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Filed May 30, 2018 John Martin Pope, Pope & Associates, PC, Suite 216, 333 East Virginia Avenue, Phoenix, AZ 85004, Benjamin Wiesinger, Pope & Associates, PC, Suite # 220, 320 E. McDowell Rd., Phoenix, AZ 85004 for Petitioner. Aimee J. Carmichael, Trial Attorney, Aaron Nelson, Trial Attorney, Corey Leigh Farrell, OIL, DOJ-U.S. Department of Justice, Civil Division/Office of Immigration Litigation, P.O. Box 878, Benjamin Franklin Station, Washington, DC 20044, Chief Counsel ICE, Office of the Chief Counsel, Department of Homeland Security, P.O. Box 26449, San Francisco, CA 94126-6449 for Respondent. Kara Hartzler, Federal Defenders of San Diego, Inc., Suite 900, 225 Broadway, San Diego, CA 92101-5030 for Amicus Curiae Federal Defenders of San Diego, Inc. Before: Andrew J. Kleinfeld and Kim McLane Wardlaw, Circuit Judges, and Rosanna Malouf Peterson, * District Judge.

ORDER

The Honorable Rosanna Malouf Peterson, United States District Judge for the Eastern District of Washington, sitting by designation.

Petitioner's petition for panel rehearing is GRANTED and the opinion filed September 14, 2017 is WITHDRAWN . The petition for rehearing en banc is denied as moot. Submission is vacated pending further order of the court.

IT IS SO ORDERED.
